{{- if eq .Snippet "findings"}}
For each finding{{if or (eq .AgentRole "merge") (eq .AgentRole "dedupe")}}, merged or not{{end}}:
{{- if or (eq .AgentRole "merge") (eq .AgentRole "dedupe")}}
- output `id` for every finding; preserve one source `id` when keeping or merging input findings
- DO NOT generate a fresh UUID
- NEVER copy the `<uuid-v4>` placeholder
- output `verification` for every finding; keep `verification.id` equal to the output finding `id`
{{- end}}
- use ONE distinct issue per finding
- make the title imperative and less than 80 characters
- set `priority` to 0, 1, 2 or 3 (always required)
- set `confidence_score` to a value between 0 and 1 reflecting how confident you are in the finding (always required)
- keep the body matter-of-fact and EXPLICIT about the scenario where it fails
  - write it as one continuous body
  - NO headers, NO titles
  - add paragraphs, e.g. an empty line, between distinct points to improve readability
{{- if eq .AgentRole "review"}}
{{- if not .DisableSuggestions}}
  - DO NOT include the following in `body`:
    - full replacement code
    - full patches
    - or before/after patches
{{- end}}
  - put code references and symbol names in backticks or code blocks
  - format bold or italic when it makes sense to emphasize a point
{{- end}}
{{- if eq .AgentRole "review"}}
- keep `code_location.line_range` as short as possible and make sure it overlaps the diff
{{- end}}
{{- if and (eq .AgentRole "review") .HasTools}}
- ALWAYS use `find_lines` to fill every `code_location` under findings and suggestions
- copy `matches[].code_location` from `find_lines` exactly:
  - include `file_path`, `line_range.start`, `line_range.end`, `line_range.count`, and `content`
  - include `language` when present
{{- end}}
- use repo-relative paths in `code_location.file_path`; do not invent paths or include absolute paths
{{- if .DisableSuggestions}}
- do not output `suggestions`
{{- else if eq .AgentRole "review"}}
- generate one or more `suggestions` entries, each including `body` and `code_location`,
  if you think obvious fixes exist; suggestions are not required
- do not output duplicate suggestions for the same fix; if two suggestions propose the same edit,
  keep only the clearer one
{{- if .HasTools}}
- use `find_lines` for each `suggestions[].code_location`;
  this code location should identify the exact code the suggestion replaces or edits
{{- end}}
- put the following in `suggestions[].body`:
  - full replacement code
  - full patches
  - or before/after patches
{{- else if or (eq .AgentRole "merge") (eq .AgentRole "dedupe")}}
- output at most one `suggestions` entry per finding, including `body` and the full `code_location`;
  select the clearest, most actionable source suggestion and DO NOT invent new suggestions
{{- end}}
{{- end}}
{{- if eq .Snippet "priority"}}
### PRIORITY
Use these priority levels:
- 0: blocking release or major universal failure
- 1: urgent and should be fixed in the next cycle
- 2: normal bug worth fixing
- 3: low-priority issue
{{- end}}
{{- if eq .Snippet "output_format"}}
Return your response as a JSON object matching this example shape
(the fences below only delimit the example):

```json
{{.OutputSchemaSnippet}}
```

- respond with raw JSON only
- DO NOT wrap your response in markdown fences or extra prose
- match the expected response fields exactly
{{- end}}
